                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d943">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15422.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-14T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1915—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>813. Your No. 671, July 11, 1 p.m. As crisis in Mexico City has passed,
                    Department will send its 808, July 8, 6 p.m., to Carothers instead of having you
                    deliver it to Conventionists.</p>
                <p>Department gratified at splendid work done by you, in conjunction with
                    colleagues, in recent Mexico City crisis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
